    	<annotation>

        		<marginalia hand="Italian">
        			<language ident="LA">
            			<position book_orientation="0" place="head">
                    				<marginalia_text>
                    					Mea[e] vnius professiones, partim positiua[e], partim
                    					scholastica[e]: sed maximè omnium pragmatica[e]. 
                      			</marginalia_text>
            			</position>
        			</language>
        			<translation>
        				One part of my profession is positive, another part is scholastic, but in all parts it is pragmatic.
        			</translation>
        		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Definitiones, et diuisiones, è positiua 
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						methodo. Oppositiones, et distintiones è
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						scholastica Subtilitate. Arcana mundi, (
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						) è profundissimis olim veteratoribus,
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						et potentissmis hodiè nouatoribus.
    						Egregiorum Pragmaticoru[m] doctores, non
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Cuiacius, aut Ra[e]uardus: sed Bodinus Politicus,
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<person name="Jacques Cujas"/>
    					<person name="Jacobus Raevardus"/>
    					<person name="Jean Bodin"/>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						et Vegetius cum Hopperi vera
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<person name="Vegetius"/>
    					<person name="Joachim Hoppers"/>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						) Iurisprudentia:
    						Bartholus, et Baldus subtiles professores:
    						Maranta, et Durandus terribiles Pragmatici: cum
    						Locupletissimo Bertachino, qui est vnus instar Om[nium]
    							<!-- Marginalia finishes in gutter. -->
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<person name="Bartolus de Saxoferrato"/>
    					<person name="Baldus de Ubaldis"/>
    					<person name="Roberto Maranta"/>
    					<person name="Guillaume Durand"/>
    					<person name="Giovanni Bertachini"/>
    					<book title="Seduardus sive de vera iurisprudentia"/>
    					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Definitions and divisions come from positive method. Oppositions and distinctions come from
    				scholastic subtlety. The secrets of the world once came from the most profound old men, and	
    				today from the most capable young men. The doctors of distinguished pragmatic studies are not
    				Cujas or Raevardus, but Bodin, the politican, and Vegetius, together with Hopper's True Study of Law.
    				Bartolus and Baldo are subtle professors; Maranta and Durandus are venerable pragmatic men, 
    				together with Bertachini, most richly supplied, who is one equal to all others.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
